-- S. Africa Fights Back to Reach 117-0 After Australia Makes 550
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2012-11-23T04:45:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-23/s-africa-fights-back-to-reach-117-0-after-australia-makes-550.html
South Africa reached 117 without
loss after fighting back to dismiss  Australia  for 550 on day two
of their second cricket Test in Adelaide.  Touring captain Graeme Smith scored 57 not out, sharing an
unbeaten opening stand with Alviro Petersen, who was on 47 at
the tea interval.  Australia lost its last five wickets for 68 runs in the
morning session after amassing 482-5 on day one. James Pattinson
smashed 42 off 35 balls to help lift the Australians’ total
after they fell to 504-9. Home captain Michael Clarke top scored
with 230, adding six runs to his overnight score after yesterday
becoming the first batsman in elite Tests to register four
double centuries in a calendar year.  Morne Morkel finished as South Africa’s best bowler, taking
5-146 from his 30 overs, while spinner Imran Tahir went
wicketless for 180 runs in 23 overs.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
